ll,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2019-05-16T19:25:14Z","updated_at":"2019-05-20T17:57:09Z","closed_at":"2019-05-20T17:57:09Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"I tried to finally get setup with blackd running as a systemd user unit, and I'm not clear from the docs how I should be setting up the client side of this.\r\n\r\n<details><summary>I'm able to setup a working unit with this config</summary>\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ cat ~/.config/systemd/user/blackd.service\r\n[Unit]\r\nDescription=blackd autoformatting server\r\n[Service]  # installed in a virtualenv\r\nExecStart=/home/sirosen/bin/blackd-env/bin/blackd --bind-port 9090\r\n[Install]\r\nWantedBy=default.target\r\n```\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n<details><summary>and then test this with simple curl</summary>\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl -sf -XPOST localhost:9090 -d \"$(cat setup.py)\" > /dev/null; echo $?\r\n0\r\n```\r\n</details>\r\n\r\nSo it works, hooray!\r\n\r\nI wanted to start using this in pre-commit hooks and other places.\r\n\r\nI almost asked \"how do I setup `black` to call out to `blackd`?\" but that obviously defeats the whole point of blackd. How are people doing this? Is there some standard client tool in use?\r\n\r\nI think even a doc note that \"you need to write your own blackd client\" is fine, just to alleviate any confusion about this.","closed_by":{"login":"zsol","id":66740,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzQw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/66740?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/zsol","html_url":"https://github.com/zsol","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zsol/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zsol/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zsol/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"h